This code implements three solutions using semaphores for the given Problem. 

A:
    To compile WaitStudents-cs20btech11055-A:
        g++ -std=c++17 -o A WaitStudents-cs20btech11055-A.cpp -lpthread
    To run A:
        ./A
B:
    To compile WaitStudents-cs20btech11055-B:
        g++ -std=c++17 -o B WaitStudents-cs20btech11055-B.cpp -lpthread
    To run B:
        ./B

C:
    To compile WaitStudents-cs20btech11055-C:
        g++ -std=c++17 -o C WaitStudents-cs20btech11055-C.cpp -lpthread
    To run C:
        ./C

The input file should be in the files input-a.txt, input-b.txt, input-c.txt respectively in the format

input-a.txt:
m l n mu

input-b.txt:
k m n l mu

input-c.txt:
k m n l mu

Here, in the A Problem, the k is already taken to be 2, So, we don't have to give it in input file.